-- Kurita Water Reports a 38% Drop in Earnings From Year Ago
-- B y   R a n d a l l   H a c k l e y
-- 2012-10-31T17:28:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-31/kurita-water-reports-a-38-drop-in-earnings-from-year-ago.html
Kurita Water Industries Ltd. (6370) , a
Tokyo-based water-treatment system provider for homes and
businesses, said first-half profit fell 38 percent to 4.9
billion yen ($61.3 million) from a year ago as revenue was
little changed.  The shares, which rose 2 percent today, have declined 17
percent over the last 12 months. The company manufactures and
sells water-treatment equipment and products including water
purification and soil remediation systems.  Operating profit declined by almost 17 percent from a year
earlier, the company said in a statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Hackley in London at 
